{"action": "input", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    m1, m2 = divide_into_2_matrices(input_grid)\n    out = build_black_matrix()\n    out = replace_black_pixels_with_red(out, m1, m2)\n    return out\ndef build_black_matrix() -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.full((3, 3), black)\ndef replace_black_pixels_with_red(out: np.ndarray, m1: np.ndarray, m2: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    for i in range(3):\n        for j in range(3):\n            if m1[i][j] == black and m2[i][j] == black:\n                out[i][j] = red\n    return out\ndef divide_into_2_matrices(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[np.ndarray, np.ndarray]:\n    m1 = input_grid[:3, :]\n    m2 = input_grid[3:, :]\n    return (m1, m2)", "user_code": "def main(input_grid:np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n  m1, m2 = `The input_grid is a 6x3 matrix, divide it into 2 3x3 matrices and return`(input_grid)\n  out = `Build a 3x3 matrix of black`()\n  out = `for each pixel in out, if the corresponding pixels in m1 and m2 are both black, replace it with red`(out, m1, m2)\n  return out\n  ", "gpt_code": "def build_black_matrix() -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.full((3, 3), black)\ndef replace_black_pixels_with_red(out: np.ndarray, m1: np.ndarray, m2: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    for i in range(3):\n        for j in range(3):\n            if m1[i][j] == black and m2[i][j] == black:\n                out[i][j] = red\n    return out\ndef divide_into_2_matrices(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[np.ndarray, np.ndarray]:\n    m1 = input_grid[:3, :]\n    m2 = input_grid[3:, :]\n    return (m1, m2)", "holes": {"build_black_matrix": "Build a 3x3 matrix of black", "replace_black_pixels_with_red": "for each pixel in out, if the corresponding pixels in m1 and m2 are both black, replace it with red", "divide_into_2_matrices": "The input_grid is a 6x3 matrix, divide it into 2 3x3 matrices and return"}}
